    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-18T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-18T05:00:00-05:00" n="449"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d449">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/383: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Rumania</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gunther</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bucharest</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-18T13:00:00+03:00"
                            >September 18, 1939—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 7:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>212. Gafencu<note n="62" xml:id="d449fn62">Grigore Gafencu, Rumanian Minister for
                        Foreign Affairs.</note> received yesterday assurances from Molotov that the
                    Russian advance into Poland should not be considered menacing to Rumania. One
                    does not know however how little faith to place in these assurances. It all
                    depends upon what deal has already been made between Russia and Germany.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gunther</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
